Oceanographer: I study oceans and how they change.
I work on ships or in aircraft and get data from floats and satellites.
See the lithograph, "Global Sea Surface Temperature."
11.
Volcanologist: Using ground instruments, I study volcanoes and how they influence the climate.
I use satellite and robots to gather data when the volcanoes are active and become too dangerous to go near.
12.
Planetologist: I study planets other than Earth.
When I compare planets like Mars, which has very little water compared to Earth, I can learn more about what could happen to our planet.
The only way I can study Mars is by observing the planet with large telescopes or using data collected by satellites, such as that obtained by Voyager.
Compare the lithograph of Earth from space with the litho, "Viking Orbiter 1 Mars Mosaic."
