Rapid increases in phytoplankton biomass are known as "blooms."
In the tropics, "blooms," are stimulated by upwelling of cool, nutrient-rich subsurface waters.
"Blooms" in temperate and polar seas are caused by a different mechanism.
What factor stimulates these seasonal blooms in temperate and polar seas? Remember that phytoplankton are plants and have certain requirements.
